main event: On 18 April 1956 in Traverse City, Michigan, a deep yellow round object with a red tail was observed, appearing as a brilliant light in the west and moving north and south.
interesting points: The object was described as a deep yellow with a red tail, appearing as a brilliant light in the west and moving in a north-south direction.
The observation lasted from 0233 to 0232Z, with the object being at a very high altitude and fading out to the north by 0432Z.
The witnesses, Mr. and Mrs. Wuujan, reported clear weather conditions with clear skies and high altitude winds at 3333 feet.
The report mentions that the object has been seen in the area for the past six weeks, leading to inconclusive conclusions about its nature, possibly being the planet Venus.
The report also contains detailed weather and altitude data, as well as the opinion of the reporting officer about the object.
sighted object: deep yellow round object with a red tail
